WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:38.500 --> 00:00:43.078
We have a midcourse deviation.
Target heading 036. 1 26 miles.

3
00:00:43.338 --> 00:00:46.174
bearing 062. Havana VOR.

4
00:00:51.680 --> 00:00:54.883
He's landing at Cray Key.
Advise Key West Drug Enforcement.

5
00:00:55.017 --> 00:00:59.311
Roger. sir. AWACS to Key West. Key West
Drug Enforcement. please come in.

6
00:00:59.437 --> 00:01:03.816
If they hurry. they just
might be able to grab the bastard.

7
00:01:11.366 --> 00:01:14.036
Now. you're sure you've got the ring?

8
00:01:15.287 --> 00:01:17.410
Relax. Felix.

9
00:01:23.712 --> 00:01:26.963
- Friends of yours?
- My partners at the DEA.

10
00:01:40.605 --> 00:01:44.353
- What the hell is going on?
- Sanchez is in the Bahamas.

11
00:01:44.484 --> 00:01:47.235
- Have you cleared it?
- We've got the green light.

12
00:01:47.361 --> 00:01:50.398
Hey. Felix!
Haven't you forgotten something?

13
00:01:51.199 --> 00:01:55.493
- James. Explain to Della. will you?
- No way. I'm coming with you.

14
00:01:55.620 --> 00:01:58.989
OK. but strictly as an observer.

15
00:01:59.124 --> 00:02:01.163
- Sorry. Sharky.
- Hey. why me?

16
00:02:01.292 --> 00:02:06.535
Hey. you guys. you can't do this to me.
What will I tell Della?

17
00:02:27.527 --> 00:02:30.362
What did he promise you? His heart?

18
00:02:32.991 --> 00:02:35.030
Give her his heart.

19
00:02:35.410 --> 00:02:39.076
No. No. Franz. I didn't mean any harm.

20
00:02:41.833 --> 00:02:44.407
It's all right. baby. No te preocupes.

21
00:02:46.839 --> 00:02:49.294
We all make mistakes.

22
00:02:51.844 --> 00:02:54.928
- Your escapades are getting creative.
- Por favor. Franz.

23
00:02:55.055 --> 00:02:57.095
Not a word.

24
00:03:15.326 --> 00:03:18.445
He's still not here.
Can you go around the block again?

25
00:03:18.579 --> 00:03:22.872
- What about the guests?
- I told you this was a mistake.

26
00:03:26.128 --> 00:03:28.584
James. Just in case.

27
00:03:49.861 --> 00:03:51.818
OK.

28
00:04:04.418 --> 00:04:06.493
I want Sanchez alive.

29
00:04:06.628 --> 00:04:08.667
Stay here. James.

30
00:04:25.188 --> 00:04:27.228
- No Sanchez.
- Damn.

31
00:05:15.156 --> 00:05:18.987
Hey. observer.
You trying to get yourself killed?

32
00:05:19.118 --> 00:05:23.115
If I don't get you back for the wedding.
I'm a dead man for sure.

33
00:05:30.171 --> 00:05:34.464
- Do you need help?
- Take your hands off me. Just go away.

34
00:05:39.139 --> 00:05:41.973
Sanchez. Let's go.

35
00:06:04.372 --> 00:06:06.828
Come on.

36
00:06:14.716 --> 00:06:18.880
- He'll be in Cuban airspace in 20 minutes.
- He hasn't got away yet.

37
00:06:19.012 --> 00:06:22.511
- What the hell are you doing?
- Let's go fishing.

38
00:06:58.218 --> 00:07:00.591
Forward.

39
00:07:01.472 --> 00:07:05.137
Easy. Hold it. Back up.

40
00:07:11.023 --> 00:07:13.063
Forward now.

41
00:07:14.151 --> 00:07:16.689
Hold it.

42
00:07:23.369 --> 00:07:26.406
Bring him in. Take the load.

43
00:07:46.726 --> 00:07:49.182
Let's go. James.

44
00:08:26.558 --> 00:08:28.597
James. Your hat.

45
00:08:28.727 --> 00:08:30.766
Thank you.

46
00:11:32.955 --> 00:11:36.538
You're facin' 1 39 felony counts. Sanchez.

47
00:11:37.919 --> 00:11:41.204
Why. that's 936 years.

48
00:11:42.632 --> 00:11:47.009
Even one of your famous million-dollar
bribes can't get you out of this one.

49
00:11:47.136 --> 00:11:48.797
Two.

50
00:11:48.930 --> 00:11:50.887
What?

51
00:11:51.015 --> 00:11:53.553
Two million. US.

52
00:11:53.685 --> 00:11:57.303
A standing offer
for anyone who springs me.

53
00:11:57.438 --> 00:12:01.650
Goddamn it. You think
you're in some banana republic?

54
00:12:01.777 --> 00:12:04.563
All that scumbag money
won't do you a bit of good here.

55
00:12:04.696 --> 00:12:07.318
Very good.
But I think I'm gonna be home soon.

56
00:12:07.616 --> 00:12:11.031
- Why. you...
- Get hold of yourself.

57
00:12:13.664 --> 00:12:16.830
We got a nice private cell
waiting for your ass at Quantico.

58
00:12:17.167 --> 00:12:20.085
And I'm gonna personally
see you get there.

59
00:12:22.213 --> 00:12:24.669
I'm terribly sorry.

60
00:12:26.551 --> 00:12:29.967
That's a custom. The bride
always gets to kiss her best man.

61
00:12:32.057 --> 00:12:34.892
I thought it was the other way round.

62
00:12:36.645 --> 00:12:40.856
James. would you mind? Felix is still
in the study and we've got to cut the cake.

63
00:12:40.983 --> 00:12:45.146
- I'll do anything for a woman with a knife.
- Thank you. Could you help me?

64
00:12:56.082 --> 00:12:58.999
- Sorry.
- No. we're finished. Pam. meet James.

65
00:12:59.126 --> 00:13:00.786
Goodbye. Felix.

66
00:13:04.631 --> 00:13:07.966
- Strictly business. my friend.
- Switch that thing off. Felix.

67
00:13:08.094 --> 00:13:12.138
- You have a house full of guests waiting.
- Just let me save this. Take a seat.

68
00:13:12.265 --> 00:13:17.259
The department wants a full report -
yesterday. We really hit it lucky today.

69
00:13:17.603 --> 00:13:20.142
Sanchez hasn't been out
of his home base for years.

70
00:13:20.272 --> 00:13:23.855
- Couldn't you extradite him?
- He's killed. intimidated or bribed

71
00:13:23.985 --> 00:13:26.356
half the officials from here to Chile.

72
00:13:26.487 --> 00:13:29.441
There's only one law
down there - Sanchez's law.

73
00:13:31.785 --> 00:13:33.693
Lead or silver.

74
00:13:34.537 --> 00:13:35.700
Ed.

75
00:13:35.830 --> 00:13:38.367
Double congratulations. old buddy.

76
00:13:38.499 --> 00:13:41.915
You take your time on the honeymoon.
Everything's OK.

77
00:13:42.045 --> 00:13:45.378
You must be Bond.
The guy who came along for the ride.

78
00:13:45.756 --> 00:13:47.714
Ed Killifer.

79
00:13:47.842 --> 00:13:50.926
We're takin' Sanchez
to Quantico this afternoon.

80
00:13:51.053 --> 00:13:53.759
- Stay and have a drink with us.
- Gotta get back.

81
00:13:53.890 --> 00:13:56.427
I just came by to kiss the bride.

82
00:13:57.518 --> 00:14:02.595
- Felix. time to cut the cake.
- Hand me the picture of Della. quick.

83
00:14:06.695 --> 00:14:08.272
She must be ready to kill me.

84
00:14:15.537 --> 00:14:17.577
- I tied 'em myself.
- What are these?

85
00:14:17.706 --> 00:14:20.659
- Lures.
- These'll keep you busy for a few days.

86
00:14:20.792 --> 00:14:24.078
You're not going fishing
on my honeymoon.

87
00:14:26.256 --> 00:14:31.713
- How many others are being held there?
- Where are you taking him. Mr Killifer?

88
00:14:31.846 --> 00:14:35.428
Mr Sanchez. will you look
this way for a picture. please?

89
00:14:35.557 --> 00:14:38.890
- Come on. Get him inside.
- What is your real nationality?

90
00:14:39.019 --> 00:14:42.519
- Are you really Colombian?
- Have you been fairly treated?

91
00:14:42.648 --> 00:14:44.141
One more picture.

92
00:14:44.274 --> 00:14:47.644
Are you connected with
any laboratories in South America?

93
00:14:47.778 --> 00:14:52.107
- No more questions. now.
- Do you expect to be vindicated?

94
00:14:55.703 --> 00:14:58.158
OK. let's go.

95
00:15:18.309 --> 00:15:20.681
Would you excuse me just a minute?

96
00:15:20.811 --> 00:15:24.856
I have a surprise for you.
Yes. I do. It's right over here.

97
00:15:26.734 --> 00:15:28.774
What's that?

98
00:15:35.284 --> 00:15:38.368
James. Love always. Della and Felix.

99
00:15:38.496 --> 00:15:40.952
We love you.

100
00:15:41.082 --> 00:15:43.122
Thanks.

101
00:16:17.911 --> 00:16:19.654
Come on.

102
00:16:46.482 --> 00:16:48.724
What the hell's happened?

103
00:16:50.152 --> 00:16:52.228
How deep is it there?

104
00:16:52.738 --> 00:16:55.194
Call up an amphibian.

105
00:17:30.235 --> 00:17:34.612
James. I wanted you to have something.

106
00:17:34.739 --> 00:17:39.733
You know the tradition? The next one
who catches this is the next one who...

107
00:17:39.869 --> 00:17:42.242
No.

108
00:17:42.372 --> 00:17:45.622
Thanks. Della. It's time I left.

109
00:17:46.209 --> 00:17:47.668
James.

110
00:17:56.219 --> 00:17:59.386
- Did I say something wrong?
- He was married once.

111
00:17:59.514 --> 00:18:01.969
But it was a long time ago.

112
00:18:07.939 --> 00:18:11.355
Felix. you're no good to me
with a wrecked back.

113
00:18:21.036 --> 00:18:23.788
Let her go. I'm the one you want.

114
00:18:38.261 --> 00:18:41.132
Ready? We got the batteries
recharged on the sub.

115
00:18:41.265 --> 00:18:45.428
It'll take you to the limit. Fast boat
to Cuba. You'll be there for breakfast.

116
00:18:45.561 --> 00:18:49.143
- Relax. We'll wait for Dario.
- Look. are you crazy?

117
00:18:49.272 --> 00:18:55.145
You got everybody lookin' for you. What
about Killifer? Havin' a cop here is nuts.

118
00:18:56.321 --> 00:18:59.276
I wanna deep six him.

119
00:18:59.408 --> 00:19:02.195
I made a deal with this guy.
and I'm gonna keep my word.

120
00:19:02.453 --> 00:19:07.695
I don't like it. He can finger me.
I spent a fortune on this cover.

121
00:19:09.877 --> 00:19:13.246
Something you'd better
understand. amigo.

122
00:19:14.173 --> 00:19:17.589
Loyalty is more important
to me than money.

123
00:19:18.052 --> 00:19:20.091
Now get the cop.

124
00:19:22.473 --> 00:19:24.513
Killifer.

125
00:19:29.189 --> 00:19:34.100
Here's two million. All in twenties.
It's very heavy. but difficult to trace.

126
00:19:34.235 --> 00:19:36.442
- Smart.
- Now. be ready for tomorrow.

127
00:19:36.570 --> 00:19:38.610
I'll have someone pick you up.

128
00:19:38.739 --> 00:19:40.863
- Where's Lupe?
- On the boat.

129
00:19:40.992 --> 00:19:43.661
Keep her there until I send for her.

130
00:19:46.456 --> 00:19:49.409
Hey. no foolin' around with my girl.

131
00:19:49.542 --> 00:19:52.876
Are you kiddin'? After what you did
to that guy on the islands?

132
00:19:53.004 --> 00:19:55.542
You liked my little valentine. huh?

133
00:20:23.702 --> 00:20:27.118
- Where's my wife?
- Don't worry.

134
00:20:27.247 --> 00:20:29.786
We gave her a nice honeymoon.

135
00:20:38.550 --> 00:20:41.754
I want you to know
this is nothing personal.

136
00:20:41.887 --> 00:20:44.757
It's purely business.

137
00:21:11.000 --> 00:21:11.830
Killifer?

138
00:21:11.960 --> 00:21:16.289
Sorry. old buddy. but two mill
is a hell of a chunk of dough.

139
00:21:21.552 --> 00:21:24.921
Killing me won't stop anything. Sanchez.

140
00:21:25.055 --> 00:21:28.140
There are worse things
than dying. hombre.

141
00:21:35.567 --> 00:21:37.938
See you in hell!

142
00:21:38.069 --> 00:21:41.818
No. Today is the first day
of the rest of your life.

143
00:21:44.534 --> 00:21:46.610
No!

144
00:22:22.281 --> 00:22:24.320
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

145
00:22:25.659 --> 00:22:28.494
Thank you. Your passport. please.

146
00:22:32.290 --> 00:22:36.158
- What's going on?
- Some big drug dealer just escaped.

147
00:22:37.212 --> 00:22:40.213
Now. would that be smoking
or nonsmoking. Mr...

148
00:22:40.591 --> 00:22:41.457
Your ticket.

149
00:23:09.453 --> 00:23:11.493
Felix?

150
00:23:25.094 --> 00:23:27.134
Della.

151
00:24:28.033 --> 00:24:31.817
- Della?
- Felix. You'll be all right. Hang on.

152
00:24:35.916 --> 00:24:40.543
- Hey. Leiter. Where you been?
- It's Bond. Get an ambulance here. quick.

153
00:24:50.139 --> 00:24:52.048
Hi. Sharky.

154
00:24:52.183 --> 00:24:55.966
You stick around. I might have
some more questions for you. OK?

155
00:24:56.103 --> 00:24:58.143
How is he?

156
00:24:58.648 --> 00:25:02.645
His left leg's gone below the knee.
They might be able to save his arm.

157
00:25:02.777 --> 00:25:06.904
You can bet it was a chain saw.
Colombians use them on informers.

158
00:25:07.031 --> 00:25:10.946
Hell. they sell more here
than in the state of Oregon.

159
00:25:11.368 --> 00:25:15.616
I wish I could be more hopeful.
but we'll have to wait and see.

160
00:25:16.875 --> 00:25:21.038
Chain saw. my ass.
I know a shark bite when I see one.

161
00:25:29.011 --> 00:25:32.096
Sanchez has vanished.
He's got all of Leiter's files.

162
00:25:32.223 --> 00:25:35.058
- God only knows what's in them.
- Well. find him.

163
00:25:35.184 --> 00:25:39.432
He's out of our jurisdiction. There's plenty
of countries that would protect him.

164
00:25:39.564 --> 00:25:43.063
- We can't even get an extradition.
- There are other ways.

165
00:25:43.192 --> 00:25:46.063
- Let it go. Commander.
- You're gonna do nothing?

166
00:25:46.196 --> 00:25:50.407
- You're just gonna forget all about it?
- No. I'm not gonna forget about it.

167
00:25:50.533 --> 00:25:54.910
Looks like Sanchez' law
operates north of the border. too.

168
00:25:55.038 --> 00:25:57.494
Let's go shark-hunting.

169
00:26:03.797 --> 00:26:08.375
This is the last place in the Keys.
We'll have to try Miami next.

170
00:26:08.510 --> 00:26:10.550
Stay here.

171
00:26:22.650 --> 00:26:25.567
You stay out of sight. I'll handle this.

172
00:26:32.826 --> 00:26:35.399
We're closed. Ain't nobody here.

173
00:26:35.537 --> 00:26:38.574
Look. I've come all the way
from London to see you.

174
00:26:38.707 --> 00:26:41.376
Universal Exports. We've been retained

175
00:26:41.501 --> 00:26:44.419
to arrange shipment
of a Carcharodon carcharias.

176
00:26:44.672 --> 00:26:46.829
- A what?
- Great white shark.

177
00:26:46.965 --> 00:26:49.670
It's all right. Bill. Let him in.

178
00:26:49.802 --> 00:26:52.921
Unfortunately.
we sold all our sharks years ago.

179
00:26:53.055 --> 00:26:57.682
As you can see. we do purely research
now. It's a project to feed the Third World.

180
00:26:57.810 --> 00:27:02.805
We feed maggot to our special breed
of genetically engineered fish.

181
00:27:02.940 --> 00:27:06.890
Use hormones to make them all male -
gain weight faster.

182
00:27:12.324 --> 00:27:15.160
From your shark-hunting days?

183
00:27:15.286 --> 00:27:17.408
Yeah. Actually. it's for sale.

184
00:27:17.538 --> 00:27:20.623
Look. I'm kinda busy.
Maybe some other time.

185
00:27:25.046 --> 00:27:28.415
Thank you. I'll look forward
to seeing you again.

186
00:27:28.549 --> 00:27:31.123
- Goodbye. Mr...
- Goodbye.

187
00:28:04.585 --> 00:28:08.750
Mr Krest said to be ready. He'll send the
sub back in three hours to pick you up.

188
00:28:08.882 --> 00:28:10.921
Can't wait.

189
00:28:11.050 --> 00:28:13.506
This dump gives me the creeps.

190
00:28:24.648 --> 00:28:26.475
James.

191
00:29:49.359 --> 00:29:51.815
Hold it right there.

192
00:30:01.997 --> 00:30:04.666
Do you mind if I get
my hands out of here?

193
00:30:04.791 --> 00:30:07.496
Yeah. Do it slowly.

194
00:31:26.082 --> 00:31:28.323
Freeze!

195
00:31:28.459 --> 00:31:30.535
Over by the trap door. old buddy.

196
00:31:38.345 --> 00:31:41.049
Is this where you put
your old buddy Felix?

197
00:31:41.180 --> 00:31:45.557
Not me. Chalk that one up
to Sanchez and Krest.

198
00:32:10.752 --> 00:32:14.537
There's two million dollars
in that suitcase.

199
00:32:14.673 --> 00:32:17.128
I'll split it with you.

200
00:32:23.932 --> 00:32:26.009
You earned it.

201
00:32:26.143 --> 00:32:28.812
You keep it. old buddy.

202
00:32:43.077 --> 00:32:45.650
God. what a terrible waste.

203
00:32:47.331 --> 00:32:49.490
Of money.

204
00:32:54.171 --> 00:32:56.211
Hey. Sharky.

205
00:32:57.591 --> 00:33:01.210
- Any news on the Wavekrest?
- She's a big marine-research vessel.

206
00:33:01.345 --> 00:33:03.468
owned by a Milton Krest.

207
00:33:03.597 --> 00:33:07.132
They're collecting specimens
off the Cay Sel Bank.

208
00:33:07.268 --> 00:33:12.262
- How long will it take us to get there?
- Maybe about six hours.

209
00:33:12.398 --> 00:33:15.601
I've a few things to pick up.
Be ready in an hour.

210
00:33:20.782 --> 00:33:23.107
Hey. Commander. You got a minute?

211
00:33:24.202 --> 00:33:27.202
Local cops got a tip
about a warehouse last night.

212
00:33:27.329 --> 00:33:31.244
Turned up 500 keys of Colombian pure.
a couple of stiffs.

213
00:33:31.376 --> 00:33:34.460
and a little bitty piece
of what used to be Killifer.

214
00:33:34.587 --> 00:33:37.458
Good. At least someone's on the case.

215
00:33:37.591 --> 00:33:41.089
You may be a pal of Leiter's.
but I can only cover up so much.

216
00:33:41.219 --> 00:33:43.675
The DEA is screaming
to know what happened.

217
00:33:43.805 --> 00:33:47.553
You know. we got laws
in this country. too.

218
00:33:47.684 --> 00:33:51.183
Do you have a law against
what they did to Leiter?

219
00:33:55.066 --> 00:33:59.693
Look. you're in over your head.
This is where it ends. Commander.

220
00:34:36.692 --> 00:34:39.479
You were supposed to be
in Istanbul last night.

221
00:34:39.611 --> 00:34:43.775
I'm afraid this unfortunate Leiter
business has clouded your judgment.

222
00:34:43.908 --> 00:34:47.739
You have a job to do. I expect you
on a plane this afternoon.

223
00:34:47.870 --> 00:34:50.906
- I haven't finished here. sir.
- Leave it to the Americans.

224
00:34:51.039 --> 00:34:56.165
- It's their mess. Let them clear it up.
- Sir. they're not going to do anything.

225
00:34:56.295 --> 00:35:00.375
I owe it to Leiter. He's put his life
on the line for me many times.

226
00:35:00.508 --> 00:35:04.671
Spare me this sentimental rubbish.
He knew the risks.

227
00:35:05.930 --> 00:35:09.133
- And his wife?
- This private vendetta of yours

228
00:35:09.266 --> 00:35:12.184
could easily compromise
Her Majesty's Government.

229
00:35:12.311 --> 00:35:18.350
You have an assignment. I expect you to
carry it out objectively and professionally.

230
00:35:20.153 --> 00:35:22.441
Then you have my resignation. sir.

231
00:35:22.572 --> 00:35:25.324
We're not a country club. 007.

232
00:35:29.203 --> 00:35:33.331
Effective immediately.
your licence to kill is revoked.

233
00:35:33.457 --> 00:35:36.542
and I require you
to hand over your weapon.

234
00:35:37.671 --> 00:35:39.710
Now.

235
00:35:41.633 --> 00:35:46.093
I need hardly remind you that you're
still bound by the Official Secrets Act.

236
00:35:48.139 --> 00:35:50.179
Well. I guess it's

237
00:35:51.559 --> 00:35:54.015
a farewell to arms.

238
00:36:02.820 --> 00:36:05.276
Don't. Too many people.

239
00:36:10.662 --> 00:36:12.406
God help you. Commander.

240
00:36:31.434 --> 00:36:33.472
Something in Sector C.

241
00:36:45.364 --> 00:36:48.650
You caused us all
a lot of trouble. young lady.

242
00:36:48.784 --> 00:36:54.823
- You're borracho. Go to bed.
- When Sanchez heard you ran away.

243
00:36:54.957 --> 00:36:58.575
- He went nuts.
- It's none of your business.

244
00:36:59.295 --> 00:37:04.585
It's my business when your stupid
little tricks get Sanchez arrested

245
00:37:04.717 --> 00:37:08.251
and I gotta put my organisation
at risk to get him out.

246
00:37:08.387 --> 00:37:13.382
The DEA just raided Key West.
You cost me a lot of dough.

247
00:37:14.310 --> 00:37:16.931
He'll give you the money.

248
00:37:18.064 --> 00:37:22.311
He doesn't work that way.
You'd better watch yourself. girlie.

249
00:37:22.443 --> 00:37:27.782
I've known him a long time. I've seen
a lot of girls like you come and go.

250
00:37:27.907 --> 00:37:30.363
You're drunk. Get out.

251
00:37:32.620 --> 00:37:37.033
- And stop peeking through my windows.
- Come on. What are you so stuck-up for?

252
00:37:37.167 --> 00:37:40.370
He fixed that phoney
beauty contest you won.

253
00:37:41.254 --> 00:37:43.247
Mr Krest.

254
00:37:44.215 --> 00:37:45.378
Yeah. What?

255
00:37:45.508 --> 00:37:50.929
The Sentinel's picking up something large
on the monitor. You'd better take a look.

256
00:37:51.848 --> 00:37:53.888
I don't believe this.

257
00:38:01.691 --> 00:38:04.147
What the hell is it now?

258
00:38:07.615 --> 00:38:12.490
It's just a manta ray. Get the probe
back in. We'll start loading now.

259
00:38:12.619 --> 00:38:13.366
Yes. sir.

260
00:40:02.564 --> 00:40:04.604
He said "You're OK."

261
00:40:42.146 --> 00:40:44.304
Take care of him.

262
00:41:02.291 --> 00:41:04.331
Make a sound and you're dead.

263
00:41:08.380 --> 00:41:11.797
- You...
- What are you doing in here?

264
00:41:11.926 --> 00:41:16.339
- Krest gave me his cabin. He's next door.
- Where's Sanchez?

265
00:41:16.472 --> 00:41:19.592
He's not on board.
I don't know where he is.

266
00:41:19.725 --> 00:41:22.976
- You're his girlfriend.
- He doesn't tell me anything.

267
00:41:26.065 --> 00:41:29.066
Open up. I need to talk to you.

268
00:41:29.986 --> 00:41:32.144
Answer it.

269
00:41:32.280 --> 00:41:34.320
Just a moment.

270
00:41:36.951 --> 00:41:40.617
- What do you want?
- Somebody slipped aboard. Did you

271
00:41:40.747 --> 00:41:44.447
- See anybody?
- No. I was sleeping. Go away.

272
00:41:44.584 --> 00:41:47.455
Mr Krest. They're back.

273
00:41:47.587 --> 00:41:49.626
Bolt your door.

274
00:41:52.843 --> 00:41:55.760
Who whipped you? Sanchez?

275
00:41:57.430 --> 00:42:01.179
It was my fault.
I did something wrong. made him angry.

276
00:42:12.154 --> 00:42:14.609
- Nice work. Clive.
- Thanks. Mr Krest.

277
00:42:14.739 --> 00:42:17.445
Guess what? His name was Sharky.

278
00:42:19.619 --> 00:42:23.119
Get rid of the boat. We've got work to do.

279
00:42:24.375 --> 00:42:28.752
- You'd better find yourself a new lover.
- Don't you men know any other way?

280
00:42:29.088 --> 00:42:32.041
It's Sanchez' way. You seem to like it.

281
00:42:32.174 --> 00:42:37.132
You know nothing. Please go.
If they find you here. we'll both be killed.

282
00:42:39.598 --> 00:42:40.428
Stay here.

283
00:42:44.603 --> 00:42:46.845
We got everything useful out of her.

284
00:42:46.981 --> 00:42:51.109
- That's it. Take her out and sink her.
- OK. Clive. Cast off.

285
00:42:54.488 --> 00:42:56.397
Compliments of Sharky.

286
00:43:00.619 --> 00:43:02.446
Man overboard.

287
00:43:12.506 --> 00:43:14.962
Get him. Don't let him get away.

288
00:43:16.678 --> 00:43:19.678
- What's wrong?
- Get back in your cabin and stay there.

289
00:43:19.805 --> 00:43:24.597
- The guy must have drowned. Mr Krest.
- Don't be so sure. Find him.

290
00:43:34.279 --> 00:43:36.318
- Launch Sentinel.
- Yes. sir.

291
00:43:52.255 --> 00:43:54.710
Stand by to dive when I tell you.

292
00:44:06.436 --> 00:44:08.892
Numbers one and two. dive.

293
00:44:24.704 --> 00:44:27.243
I can see something reflecting over there.

294
00:44:33.756 --> 00:44:36.673
There's too much turbulence to be sure.

295
00:44:55.361 --> 00:44:58.979
- Loading completed. Mr Krest.
- Bring Sentinel back in.

296
00:45:43.284 --> 00:45:45.740
Mr Krest!

297
00:45:51.877 --> 00:45:53.537
Bring Sentinel up.

298
00:45:55.088 --> 00:45:58.125
There he is. there. Right there. Get him.

299
00:45:58.592 --> 00:46:01.213
There.

300
00:46:03.263 --> 00:46:05.718
Dive. dammit. Dive.

301
00:49:02.153 --> 00:49:03.433
There. Pick him up.

302
00:49:10.911 --> 00:49:14.495
- All boats return to Wavekrest.
- Aye aye. sir.

303
00:50:51.681 --> 00:50:54.136
Here. Put her stern-in.

304
00:51:07.488 --> 00:51:10.773
Hey. do you know
someone called Bouvier?

305
00:51:10.908 --> 00:51:12.948
Over there.

306
00:51:15.413 --> 00:51:18.283
Now. this is an unexpected pleasure.

307
00:51:18.416 --> 00:51:20.575
- Where's Leiter?
- Intensive Care.

308
00:51:20.710 --> 00:51:23.627
Where you'll be
if you don't get out of here fast.

309
00:51:23.754 --> 00:51:27.705
Sanchez has Leiter's files.
Your name's all over them.

310
00:51:28.801 --> 00:51:33.131
Hell. I knew something was wrong.
Those two have been at the bar for hours.

311
00:51:33.265 --> 00:51:37.179
- Probably waiting to see who showed up.
- Would you like anything to drink?

312
00:51:37.310 --> 00:51:39.018
- Bud with a lime.
- Same.

313
00:51:39.146 --> 00:51:41.185
Sure thing. hon.

314
00:51:43.775 --> 00:51:46.266
Shit! It's Dario.

315
00:51:46.402 --> 00:51:50.864
He's bad news. He used to be with
the Contras before they kicked him out.

316
00:51:50.991 --> 00:51:53.908
Just the kind of guy Sanchez would send.

317
00:51:55.078 --> 00:51:57.830
You carrying?

318
00:52:00.292 --> 00:52:03.293
If they start shooting.
just hit the deck and stay there.

319
00:52:19.102 --> 00:52:21.890
Don't I know you from somewhere?

320
00:52:22.022 --> 00:52:24.595
- No.
- Oh. yes. I do.

321
00:52:24.733 --> 00:52:28.351
You used to fly charter planes
for some friends of mine.

322
00:52:29.071 --> 00:52:32.820
I got a job for you. Why don't we
go outside and we talk in private?

323
00:52:32.950 --> 00:52:37.493
- Take your hands off her. She's with me.
- Nobody's asking you. gringo.

324
00:52:37.747 --> 00:52:40.830
He's with me.
Keep your hands on the table.

325
00:52:44.003 --> 00:52:46.042
Here we go.

326
00:52:46.421 --> 00:52:49.423
Two beers. That'll be 3.50.

327
00:52:49.550 --> 00:52:52.753
- Do your friends want something?
- Let me get it.

328
00:52:57.517 --> 00:53:00.720
- He's had enough. Run a tab.
- OK.

329
00:53:01.354 --> 00:53:04.936
- How did you get here?
- By boat. It's right behind this wall.

330
00:53:13.992 --> 00:53:16.031
Thanks.

331
00:54:14.428 --> 00:54:16.965
Get it started.

332
00:54:32.113 --> 00:54:33.606
Come on.

333
00:55:01.809 --> 00:55:06.222
- Don't move.
- Relax. It's a bulletproof vest.

334
00:55:06.355 --> 00:55:10.056
- This Kevlar is great.
- You're bloody lucky to be alive.

335
00:55:11.360 --> 00:55:14.196
It's not luck. It's experience.

336
00:55:14.322 --> 00:55:18.402
- Any higher. it'd have been your head.
- Look. I just saved your life back there.

337
00:55:18.534 --> 00:55:21.570
If it wasn't for me.
your ass would've been nailed to the wall.

338
00:55:21.704 --> 00:55:23.744
- You saved my life?
- Yes.

339
00:55:24.415 --> 00:55:26.907
It's a tough business
you picked. Miss Bouvier.

340
00:55:27.044 --> 00:55:30.708
- Leave it to the professionals.
- Look. pal. I was an army pilot.

341
00:55:30.839 --> 00:55:33.376
I have flown to the toughest hellholes.

342
00:55:33.507 --> 00:55:37.173
I will not have you lecture me
about professionalism.

343
00:55:46.354 --> 00:55:49.724
Out of gas. I haven't heard
that one in a long time.

344
00:55:51.567 --> 00:55:55.946
Well. they must have hit the fuel line.
Look. I'm gonna need your help.

345
00:55:56.782 --> 00:56:00.151
I want a complete rundown
on Sanchez' operation.

346
00:56:00.285 --> 00:56:05.243
And I'll need a flight to Isthmus City.
Private. No one must know I've left.

347
00:56:05.373 --> 00:56:09.620
- What do you wanna go there for?
- I'll pay you very well.

348
00:56:09.919 --> 00:56:12.921
You're going after Sanchez. aren't you?

349
00:56:13.883 --> 00:56:17.168
- Will you help me?
- How many men have you got?

350
00:56:20.598 --> 00:56:23.053
Just you and me.

351
00:56:24.143 --> 00:56:27.345
Are you crazy? Sanchez has
an entire army protecting him.

352
00:56:27.479 --> 00:56:31.429
- Just fly me in and leave. 50.000.
- It's not that easy.

353
00:56:31.567 --> 00:56:35.647
False flight plans. payoffs at the airport.
I can't do it for less than a hundred.

354
00:56:35.779 --> 00:56:37.819
Sixty.

355
00:56:39.408 --> 00:56:41.282
- Ninety.
- Seventy.

356
00:56:41.994 --> 00:56:44.450
- Eighty.
- Seventy-five.

357
00:56:45.873 --> 00:56:49.289
- You pay the fuel?
- You get the plane.

358
00:56:52.880 --> 00:56:54.920
Deal.

359
00:57:04.809 --> 00:57:09.767
- Why don't you wait until you're asked?
- Well. why don't you ask me?

360
00:57:43.557 --> 00:57:47.340
There are five typing errors on
the first page alone. What's got into you?

361
00:57:47.477 --> 00:57:49.517
Sorry. sir.

362
00:57:52.107 --> 00:57:56.733
"US lmmigration has no reports
of 007 leaving the United States

363
00:57:56.861 --> 00:57:59.317
as of 1 500 hours today."

364
00:58:00.115 --> 00:58:05.536
- Who authorised this?
- I did. sir. It's James. He's gone missing.

365
00:58:05.787 --> 00:58:09.737
You know him better than that.
He'll go after Sanchez.

366
00:58:10.375 --> 00:58:15.001
He's got to be stopped.
I've already alerted our man in Isthmus.

367
00:58:15.297 --> 00:58:18.168
- I want that out by this afternoon.
- Yes. sir.

368
00:58:20.886 --> 00:58:22.297
Q Branch. please.

369
00:58:45.703 --> 00:58:47.742
This is the master bedroom.

370
00:58:47.872 --> 00:58:51.323
- I hope everything is satisfactory. señor.
- It's adequate.

371
00:58:51.458 --> 00:58:54.246
I'd like a case of champagne -
Bollinger RD.

372
00:58:54.378 --> 00:58:57.712
Certainly. If I could ask you
to sign the registration cards?

373
00:58:57.840 --> 00:59:02.052
No. My executive secretary.
Miss Kennedy. will take care of that.

374
00:59:02.177 --> 00:59:04.503
Miss Kennedy.

375
00:59:04.639 --> 00:59:06.679
Right here. please.

376
00:59:18.945 --> 00:59:20.984
Fresh flowers every day.

377
00:59:21.113 --> 00:59:23.071
Thank you very much.

378
00:59:23.199 --> 00:59:25.655
Your key. Enjoy your stay.

379
00:59:29.748 --> 00:59:34.290
It's Ms Kennedy. And why can't you
be my executive secretary?

380
00:59:35.253 --> 00:59:39.333
We're south of the border.
It's a man's world.

381
00:59:40.175 --> 00:59:42.713
Thanks for everything.
Your job's finished.

382
00:59:42.844 --> 00:59:44.883
- I wanna stay.
- Too dangerous.

383
00:59:45.555 --> 00:59:48.675
- Enough people are dead.
- Don't talk to me about danger.

384
00:59:48.809 --> 00:59:53.684
I won't be safe until Sanchez is dead.
Besides. you could use my help.

385
00:59:57.150 --> 01:00:01.279
If you're gonna stay and be my executive
secretary. you'd better look the part.

386
01:00:01.405 --> 01:00:04.405
Here. Buy yourself some decent clothes.

387
01:00:07.077 --> 01:00:09.650
What bank does Sanchez use?
I need to make a deposit.

388
01:00:09.788 --> 01:00:13.951
The biggest one in town.
Banco de Isthmus. He owns it.

389
01:00:30.601 --> 01:00:32.640
Señor Bond.

390
01:00:35.356 --> 01:00:40.433
- I've come to make a small deposit.
- My people downstairs are capable of...

391
01:00:42.238 --> 01:00:44.029
Please. sit down.

392
01:00:44.531 --> 01:00:48.696
We operate the world's
largest private investment fund.

393
01:00:48.828 --> 01:00:53.157
Our biggest problem
is what to do with all the money.

394
01:00:53.291 --> 01:00:56.576
We have a cash surplus
of ten million a day.

395
01:00:56.710 --> 01:01:01.172
which we ship through our bank
to the US Federal Reserve.

396
01:01:01.299 --> 01:01:06.044
thus establishing credits which can
be used for any legitimate investment.

397
01:01:06.179 --> 01:01:09.927
You see. someone has to help
the gringos with their trade deficit.

398
01:01:10.057 --> 01:01:15.015
Make out a deposit receipt
for $4.900.000 for Señor Bond.

399
01:01:16.105 --> 01:01:19.723
And there will be additional
monthly deposits in the same amount.

400
01:01:19.859 --> 01:01:24.023
Of course. We are experienced in
handling accounts of this nature.

401
01:01:24.155 --> 01:01:26.194
Let me pass.

402
01:01:29.995 --> 01:01:35.369
Señor Montelongo? I'm Miss Kennedy.
Mr Bond's executive secretary.

403
01:01:35.500 --> 01:01:40.209
I'd also appreciate it if you could establish
a line of credit for me at the casino.

404
01:01:40.338 --> 01:01:42.794
- Shall we say two million dollars?
- No problem.

405
01:01:42.925 --> 01:01:47.136
You have excellent collateral.
and our chairman also owns the casino.

406
01:01:47.262 --> 01:01:52.303
- A very convenient arrangement.
- We have always thought so. señorita.

407
01:01:54.603 --> 01:01:57.972
Thank you. Good evening.
ladies and gentlemen. and welcome.

408
01:01:58.106 --> 01:02:00.146
This is a special night for us.

409
01:02:00.275 --> 01:02:03.525
We want you to know that only
through your generous donations

410
01:02:03.653 --> 01:02:06.738
can the work here at the OMI
continue to progress.

411
01:02:06.866 --> 01:02:10.945
We've learned so much.
but we've only just scratched the surface.

412
01:02:11.078 --> 01:02:15.656
We need your help. We need you to go
to your phones now and make a pledge.

413
01:02:15.791 --> 01:02:19.160
This is not for me.
This is not for them. It's for all of us.

414
01:02:19.295 --> 01:02:22.877
- Are you OK. reinita?
- I'm fine.

415
01:02:23.007 --> 01:02:27.300
Krest called me from the boat with a story
about somebody ripping him off.

416
01:02:27.428 --> 01:02:29.670
Did you see anything happen?

417
01:02:29.805 --> 01:02:33.221
No. Franz. I stayed
in my cabin most of the time.

418
01:02:36.521 --> 01:02:39.806
- What's the matter. baby?
- You know I can't stand that thing.

419
01:02:47.281 --> 01:02:50.899
- I'd like a private table. Blackjack.
- Certainly. Señor Bond.

420
01:02:51.035 --> 01:02:53.822
Would you come this way. please?

421
01:03:00.754 --> 01:03:03.588
Quarter of a million dollars.

422
01:03:03.714 --> 01:03:06.336
And I'd like to raise
the limit to 5.000 a box.

423
01:03:06.468 --> 01:03:09.801
Put these wonderful
volunteers behind me to work.

424
01:03:09.929 --> 01:03:14.390
Dario'll take you shopping. so tomorrow
you can spend a lot of money. have fun.

425
01:03:14.517 --> 01:03:16.557
Now. give me a little kiss.

426
01:03:18.480 --> 01:03:20.519
You want one too?

427
01:03:22.150 --> 01:03:25.815
We can raise the price.
22.000 per kilo this month.

428
01:03:26.696 --> 01:03:28.736
I like that.

429
01:03:30.325 --> 01:03:32.780
Yeah. this is Truman-Lodge. 22.000.

430
01:03:32.911 --> 01:03:40.242
Our goal today is to raise $22.000
from each of our meditation chapters.

431
01:03:40.377 --> 01:03:43.792
That's 22.000 each.

432
01:03:43.922 --> 01:03:48.501
Go to your phones.
Please help us. Bless your hearts.

433
01:03:55.099 --> 01:03:57.306
Let me have half a million.

434
01:03:57.436 --> 01:04:02.311
Listen to this. Our wonderful Manhattan
chapel has made a special $500 pledge.

435
01:04:02.440 --> 01:04:05.146
500 kilos. I...

436
01:04:05.277 --> 01:04:08.480
- I knew they'd go for it.
- This guy cracks me up.

437
01:04:09.197 --> 01:04:12.282
- Is Señor Sanchez there?
- Yes. he's right here.

438
01:04:15.120 --> 01:04:17.243
- Yeah?
- A British sucker dropped

439
01:04:17.373 --> 01:04:20.409
a quarter of a million
and he wants to play no limit.

440
01:04:20.542 --> 01:04:25.251
- Which one?
- Table two. Plays like a real jerk-off.

441
01:04:26.757 --> 01:04:31.169
That's the guy that flew in in the private
plane. Opened an account at the bank.

442
01:04:31.303 --> 01:04:33.841
Five million dollars in cash.

443
01:04:37.726 --> 01:04:39.766
Let him play.

444
01:04:45.359 --> 01:04:47.067
Double down.

445
01:04:48.862 --> 01:04:50.902
Split.

446
01:05:14.180 --> 01:05:20.930
Listen to this. Our Chicago chapel
has received a $1.000 donor pledge.

447
01:05:21.062 --> 01:05:24.479
They all accepted the new price.

448
01:05:24.982 --> 01:05:27.474
- Señor Sanchez?
- Yes. he's right here.

449
01:05:31.948 --> 01:05:36.657
The British guy is a quarter of a million
ahead. Should I close the table?

450
01:05:39.164 --> 01:05:41.204
No.

451
01:05:44.419 --> 01:05:47.041
- Tell Lupe to come in here.
- Right.

452
01:05:51.760 --> 01:05:56.303
You have good luck tonight.
Are you gonna share any of that money?

453
01:06:06.483 --> 01:06:09.057
Miss Kennedy.
get me a medium-dry vodka martini.

454
01:06:09.194 --> 01:06:12.894
- Why don't you ask...
- Shaken. not stirred.

455
01:06:13.824 --> 01:06:15.864
Cut.

456
01:06:25.586 --> 01:06:28.836
- You're very professional.
- Used to work here.

457
01:06:28.965 --> 01:06:33.294
- Am I going to win or lose?
- Lose. But not much.

458
01:06:36.014 --> 01:06:40.343
- Vodka martini qué?
- Shaken. not stirred.

459
01:06:40.476 --> 01:06:42.801
Ah. si.

460
01:06:42.936 --> 01:06:45.179
Looks like your luck has changed.

461
01:06:45.648 --> 01:06:49.182
- Is that why he sent you?
- And to find out more about you.

462
01:06:49.318 --> 01:06:52.023
Perhaps I'd better quit for the night.

463
01:06:55.574 --> 01:07:00.782
You should walk straight out of here.
go to the airport and never come back.

464
01:07:06.710 --> 01:07:10.127
- Where's Sanchez?
- Upstairs in his office.

465
01:07:10.256 --> 01:07:15.002
He's been there all day. He's planning a
party for some Orientals tomorrow night.

466
01:07:15.136 --> 01:07:17.628
And what did you tell him
about the Wavekrest?

467
01:07:17.764 --> 01:07:20.219
Nothing. Now go.

468
01:07:23.895 --> 01:07:27.229
- Take me to him.
- Are you loco? You'll get us both killed.

469
01:07:55.552 --> 01:07:57.592
This way. please.

470
01:08:00.432 --> 01:08:04.929
Send us a dollar. Send us 50 cents.
Send whatever you can send.

471
01:08:05.062 --> 01:08:09.356
We've got a very special offer. You guys
out there. with your beer and popcorn...

472
01:08:11.736 --> 01:08:13.644
This is almost over.

473
01:08:13.779 --> 01:08:18.820
This particular book has sold
in excess of a quarter of a million copies.

474
01:08:18.950 --> 01:08:22.700
Anyone who sends in a $1 00 pledge

475
01:08:22.830 --> 01:08:26.412
will receive a personally
autographed copy of my book.

476
01:08:26.542 --> 01:08:28.582
Lovely view.

477
01:08:29.170 --> 01:08:35.208
It's a 49.95 value.
and you get it absolutely free.

478
01:08:35.343 --> 01:08:38.628
- Bond. James Bond.
- Sit. Please.

479
01:08:38.763 --> 01:08:41.846
We need your help. Bless your hearts.

480
01:08:52.443 --> 01:08:54.898
Well-travelled man.

481
01:08:56.155 --> 01:08:58.943
You did all right at the tables tonight.

482
01:08:59.075 --> 01:09:02.111
I had the feeling
my luck was about to change.

483
01:09:02.245 --> 01:09:07.487
Well. it's a wise gambler who knows
when his luck has run out. Why this?

484
01:09:07.625 --> 01:09:09.951
In my business.
you prepare for the unexpected.

485
01:09:10.086 --> 01:09:14.629
- And what business is that?
- I help people with problems.

486
01:09:16.134 --> 01:09:18.173
Problem solver.

487
01:09:18.302 --> 01:09:20.628
More of a problem eliminator.

488
01:09:34.236 --> 01:09:38.565
- And are you here on business?
- No. temporarily unemployed.

489
01:09:40.075 --> 01:09:42.114
I thought I might find work here.

490
01:09:42.243 --> 01:09:47.202
Well. it's very difficult to obtain
a work permit in Isthmus. It's...

491
01:09:47.333 --> 01:09:52.291
Well. one has to show a special talent
that people here don't have.

492
01:09:54.255 --> 01:09:57.292
Well. that shouldn't be too difficult.

493
01:09:58.552 --> 01:10:01.256
Señor Bond. you've got big cojones.

494
01:10:02.306 --> 01:10:06.350
You come here. to my place.
without references.

495
01:10:06.476 --> 01:10:10.012
carrying a piece.
throwing around a lot of money.

496
01:10:10.147 --> 01:10:15.023
But you should know something.
Nobody saw you come in.

497
01:10:15.152 --> 01:10:17.821
so nobody has to see you go out.

498
01:10:19.615 --> 01:10:24.193
Señor Sanchez. I could be very useful
to a man in your position.

499
01:10:25.329 --> 01:10:29.872
And I understand you have a reputation
for rewarding loyalty very well.

500
01:10:33.004 --> 01:10:37.167
I'll keep this for a few days.
We'll talk again.

501
01:10:37.299 --> 01:10:41.760
And you won't need a gun in Isthmus.
It's a very safe city.

502
01:10:41.887 --> 01:10:45.932
In the meantime. I welcome you
to the casino at all times.

503
01:10:56.444 --> 01:10:57.393
Check him out.

504
01:11:00.364 --> 01:11:03.734
- So what did you find out?
- There's two inches of armoured glass.

505
01:11:03.868 --> 01:11:06.323
I'd need a cannon to get to him.

506
01:11:22.721 --> 01:11:25.971
Señor Bond. You will be pleased
to know your uncle has arrived.

507
01:11:26.099 --> 01:11:28.555
I put him in your suite.

508
01:11:29.894 --> 01:11:31.223
Thank you.

509
01:11:31.813 --> 01:11:33.853
Good night.

510
01:11:36.609 --> 01:11:40.477
- Your uncle?
- Let's make this a proper family reunion.

511
01:11:40.614 --> 01:11:42.939
Give me your gun.

512
01:12:06.223 --> 01:12:08.263
Stay here.

513
01:12:26.994 --> 01:12:30.493
- Really. 007!
- Q! What the hell are you doing here?

514
01:12:30.622 --> 01:12:33.328
- I might have killed you.
- Well. I'm on leave.

515
01:12:33.459 --> 01:12:36.495
Thought I'd pop round
and see how you were getting on.

516
01:12:36.629 --> 01:12:38.622
- Are you all right?
- Of course.

517
01:12:38.756 --> 01:12:42.540
- How'd you find me?
- Moneypenny. She's worried about you.

518
01:12:42.676 --> 01:12:46.378
- This is no place for you. Q. Go home.
- Don't be an idiot. 007.

519
01:12:46.514 --> 01:12:50.215
I know exactly what you're up to.
and you're gonna need my help.

520
01:12:50.351 --> 01:12:54.431
Remember. if it hadn't been for Q Branch.
you'd have been dead long ago.

521
01:12:55.273 --> 01:12:57.978
Everything for a man on holiday.

522
01:12:58.109 --> 01:13:02.154
Explosive alarm clock. guaranteed
never to wake up anybody who uses it.

523
01:13:03.406 --> 01:13:07.404
Dentonite toothpaste.
To be used sparingly.

524
01:13:07.535 --> 01:13:11.367
- It's the latest in plastic explosive.
- I could do with some plastic.

525
01:13:14.793 --> 01:13:17.912
I thought there might be
a mess to clean up.

526
01:13:18.880 --> 01:13:23.376
Pam. this is Q. my uncle.
Uncle. this is Miss Kennedy. my cousin.

527
01:13:23.509 --> 01:13:26.131
- We must be related.
- How do you do?

528
01:13:26.263 --> 01:13:28.718
Now. pay attention. 007.

529
01:13:30.225 --> 01:13:33.594
Now. this looks like
an ordinary camera. doesn't it?

530
01:13:33.729 --> 01:13:38.889
- What kind of film does it take? 1 20?
- .220 high velocity.

531
01:13:39.693 --> 01:13:45.529
Now. this is a signature gun.
and that is an optical palm reader.

532
01:13:46.033 --> 01:13:50.244
And if I plug this
into the bottom like that.

533
01:13:50.370 --> 01:13:52.612
once I've programmed it...

534
01:13:56.251 --> 01:13:58.956
Now. nobody can use the gun but you.

535
01:13:59.087 --> 01:14:01.757
- Smile. boys.
- Don't use the flash!

536
01:14:08.138 --> 01:14:12.088
Stop fiddling with things you don't
understand. You might have killed him.

537
01:14:12.226 --> 01:14:13.637
That's odd.

538
01:14:16.354 --> 01:14:21.979
Look. let's all get some rest. We've got
a long. hard day ahead of us tomorrow.

539
01:14:22.569 --> 01:14:25.440
- Good night. Q.
- Sweet dreams. Mr Bond.

540
01:14:31.912 --> 01:14:34.036
I hope you don't snore. Q.

541
01:14:39.545 --> 01:14:42.250
You all know Truman-Lodge.

542
01:14:42.381 --> 01:14:45.965
And this is my head of security
Colonel Heller.

543
01:14:50.139 --> 01:14:52.511
This is an historic moment.

544
01:14:52.641 --> 01:14:56.141
East meets West.
Drug dealers of the world unite.

545
01:15:01.109 --> 01:15:05.901
Extra bonus. Your job's done.
Take Q and fly out of here now.

546
01:15:06.030 --> 01:15:08.356
I'll make my own way back.

547
01:15:08.491 --> 01:15:10.946
I'd like to stay.

548
01:15:11.077 --> 01:15:12.737
No.

549
01:15:12.870 --> 01:15:15.327
I work better alone.

550
01:16:33.077 --> 01:16:38.072
In this business. there's a lot of cash.
And a lot of people with their hands out.

551
01:16:38.207 --> 01:16:40.698
In a word: bribery.

552
01:16:40.834 --> 01:16:43.955
Exactly. He took the words
right out of my pocket.

553
01:16:46.382 --> 01:16:51.175
So you pay. Everyone and his brother
is on the payroll.

554
01:16:53.764 --> 01:16:57.892
So you buy a mayor.
a chief of police. a general...

555
01:17:02.732 --> 01:17:07.608
A president. One day you wake up
and you own the whole goddamn country.

556
01:17:07.737 --> 01:17:12.565
Then you take what you want. A bank.
a gambling casino. airline concession.

557
01:17:13.451 --> 01:17:16.405
Why? Simple.

558
01:17:16.537 --> 01:17:20.785
It's easier for the politicians
to take silver than lead.

559
01:17:21.251 --> 01:17:25.414
We have an invisible empire
from Chile to Alaska.

560
01:17:27.507 --> 01:17:31.042
What I want to do. amigos.
is to make you part of it.

561
01:17:32.346 --> 01:17:35.595
I want the Pacific to be our little puddle.

562
01:17:38.060 --> 01:17:41.428
What you have before you
is a demographic report.

563
01:17:41.563 --> 01:17:47.648
breaking down each of your territories
by age and socioeconomic group.

564
01:17:48.195 --> 01:17:52.655
Now. as you can clearly see.
there is a huge potential demand.

565
01:17:52.782 --> 01:17:56.033
given the implementation
of aggressive marketing.

566
01:17:56.161 --> 01:17:58.034
As in the United States.

567
01:17:58.163 --> 01:18:02.873
Señor Sanchez is prepared to offer
each of you exclusive franchises.

568
01:18:03.002 --> 01:18:06.833
The price is 100 million per territory.

569
01:18:07.965 --> 01:18:14.549
I believe you'll find that works out
to 20 million per metric ton. Mr Tan.

570
01:18:33.824 --> 01:18:37.953
We guarantee quality
and price for five years.

571
01:18:38.913 --> 01:18:46.078
Señor Sanchez. since arriving. we've
eaten well. heard many good stories.

572
01:18:46.212 --> 01:18:51.039
but before I pay anything.
I want to see some hardware.

573
01:18:51.175 --> 01:18:55.754
Mr Kwang. you don't pay for hardware.

574
01:18:56.139 --> 01:18:58.974
You pay for my personal
guarantee and protection.

575
01:18:59.100 --> 01:19:04.521
Surely if you were to invest 100 million.
you would want some reassurance.

576
01:19:07.067 --> 01:19:12.986
You're right. Why not? Tomorrow I'll take
you to our main distribution centre.

577
01:19:17.911 --> 01:19:19.951
Here you are.

578
01:19:21.372 --> 01:19:24.908
- Goodbye. Q. Thanks for all you've done.
- What?

579
01:19:26.169 --> 01:19:31.246
You're a hell of a field operative.
Now go. I'll see you back in London.

580
01:19:38.973 --> 01:19:42.592
No more business.
Time to have some fun.

581
01:19:42.769 --> 01:19:45.224
Gentlemen. enjoy yourselves.

582
01:20:00.579 --> 01:20:03.414
This Kwang seems like trouble.

583
01:20:03.540 --> 01:20:05.747
Why show them the labs?

584
01:20:05.876 --> 01:20:09.873
Don't worry.
He won't expose the operation.

585
01:20:33.529 --> 01:20:36.198
His Excellency. el presidente Lopez.

586
01:20:55.218 --> 01:21:00.425
There's been a mistake with my cheque.
Look at it. It's half the usual amount.

587
01:21:00.557 --> 01:21:04.139
You were very quiet when I was arrested.

588
01:21:05.520 --> 01:21:09.469
Remember. you're only president for life.

589
01:21:36.093 --> 01:21:39.378
Watch the birdie. you bastard.

590
01:22:36.946 --> 01:22:39.271
Take his arm.

591
01:22:44.870 --> 01:22:47.907
- Who would have a signature gun?
- James Bond.

592
01:22:52.587 --> 01:22:55.458
This is Her Majesty's Government's.
How did you get it?

593
01:22:55.590 --> 01:22:57.878
- Piss off.
- Who ordered you to kill Sanchez?

594
01:22:58.009 --> 01:23:03.050
No one. He's a rogue agent. My orders
are to take him back one way or the other.

595
01:23:03.180 --> 01:23:06.135
We're Hong Kong Narcotics. you bastard.

596
01:23:06.267 --> 01:23:09.221
Sanchez is taking us
to the heart of his operations.

597
01:23:09.353 --> 01:23:11.726
I've been setting it up for years.

598
01:23:11.856 --> 01:23:15.854
I just hope that little stunt of yours
hasn't scared him off.

599
01:23:19.864 --> 01:23:22.699
- Get me out of these bloody things.
- No. Commander.

600
01:23:22.826 --> 01:23:27.701
You're a loose cannon on deck.
I'm shipping you straight back to London.

601
01:23:33.795 --> 01:23:35.254
- Leave him.
- No.

602
01:23:35.380 --> 01:23:36.460
Come on.

603
01:23:58.320 --> 01:24:00.776
Don't let them take you alive.

604
01:24:43.449 --> 01:24:45.489
He's still alive.

605
01:24:48.037 --> 01:24:50.492
Who was it? Who sent you?

606
01:24:54.419 --> 01:24:56.458
Cyanide.

607
01:26:07.325 --> 01:26:09.365
Hey. amigo.

608
01:26:16.919 --> 01:26:19.291
How do you feel?

609
01:26:19.421 --> 01:26:21.580
I'll survive.

610
01:26:21.715 --> 01:26:23.755
Lupe. Please.

611
01:26:27.513 --> 01:26:31.427
The Wavekrest is arriving tonight.
Krest is coming here.

612
01:26:31.558 --> 01:26:34.762
No. I'll call you back.
Pedro. bring us some coffee.

613
01:26:34.896 --> 01:26:36.723
Good.

614
01:26:39.483 --> 01:26:41.523
Baby. Please.

615
01:26:51.996 --> 01:26:55.080
Well. we both had close calls last night.

616
01:26:56.042 --> 01:26:59.874
You were just in time.
Things were about to turn nasty.

617
01:27:00.005 --> 01:27:02.080
- Who were they?
- Freelance hit team.

618
01:27:02.215 --> 01:27:04.373
What did they want with you?

619
01:27:04.926 --> 01:27:08.259
One of them must have
recognised me in the casino.

620
01:27:10.014 --> 01:27:13.846
They were afraid I'd warn you.
spoil their plans.

621
01:27:13.976 --> 01:27:16.302
So you knew them?

622
01:27:17.272 --> 01:27:22.479
I used to work for the British government.
We kept dossiers on such people.

623
01:27:22.611 --> 01:27:24.982
British agent.

624
01:27:25.113 --> 01:27:27.236
I knew it.

625
01:27:29.534 --> 01:27:31.657
You have class.

626
01:27:32.746 --> 01:27:35.154
Those men tried to kill me.

627
01:27:35.791 --> 01:27:37.949
Who would do such a thing?

628
01:27:38.084 --> 01:27:40.836
- Someone close to you.
- Cream? Sugar?

629
01:27:40.963 --> 01:27:43.002
No.

630
01:27:43.465 --> 01:27:46.502
- Did they tell you this?
- They were well briefed.

631
01:27:46.635 --> 01:27:49.339
Obviously by someone on the inside.

632
01:27:51.348 --> 01:27:53.388
- Did they mention a name?
- No.

633
01:27:58.313 --> 01:28:00.851
They were expecting
to be paid a lot of cash

634
01:28:00.982 --> 01:28:04.601
by someone arriving in Isthmus tonight.

635
01:28:06.613 --> 01:28:08.820
You suspect someone?

636
01:28:08.949 --> 01:28:12.401
Everyone in my organisation
is 100 per cent loyal.

637
01:28:12.536 --> 01:28:17.744
- Then you have nothing to worry about.
- Well. I have to go meet some people.

638
01:28:19.293 --> 01:28:21.749
- You rest here.
- I have to go back to my hotel.

639
01:28:21.879 --> 01:28:26.090
No. don't go to the hotel.
Save your money. I insist.

640
01:28:26.216 --> 01:28:29.134
Stay here. Enjoy my hospitality.

641
01:28:29.262 --> 01:28:32.132
Lupe. show him the easy way up. please.

642
01:28:49.824 --> 01:28:52.398
You are not gonna believe
who this guy is.

643
01:28:55.371 --> 01:28:57.613
Former British agent.

644
01:28:58.666 --> 01:29:02.082
- How did you know that?
- Because I know things.

645
01:29:04.297 --> 01:29:08.247
I want to meet Krest's boat tonight.
We'll need a dozen reliable men.

646
01:29:08.384 --> 01:29:11.054
Is there a problem with Krest?

647
01:29:11.179 --> 01:29:16.256
We'll see. And bring Lupe. She was there.
He's not gonna lie in front of her.

648
01:29:20.772 --> 01:29:24.354
- What are you doing?
- I've had my fill of Sanchez' hospitality.

649
01:29:24.484 --> 01:29:26.690
He said to stay. You're asking for trouble.

650
01:29:26.820 --> 01:29:30.864
There's no need for you to get involved.
Just give me five minutes. then scream.

651
01:29:30.990 --> 01:29:35.452
James. listen to me. There's guards
all over the place. You'll never make it.

652
01:30:07.694 --> 01:30:10.233
I'm going shopping. I won't be long.

653
01:30:10.364 --> 01:30:13.649
Please don't. Not now.
Señor Sanchez said.

654
01:30:31.594 --> 01:30:36.718
- I haven't had one of these in five years.
- Don't worry. 007 always comes back.

655
01:30:41.020 --> 01:30:43.262
- James.
- I thought I told you to leave. Q.

656
01:30:43.397 --> 01:30:46.315
We couldn't go without knowing
what had happened to you.

657
01:30:46.442 --> 01:30:49.811
- Get your bags packed. Q.
- What the hell is the matter with you?

658
01:30:49.946 --> 01:30:53.778
Just a couple of things. Kwang
and his team of British agents are dead.

659
01:30:53.908 --> 01:30:57.158
Sanchez is alive.
I saw you in Heller's office.

660
01:30:57.287 --> 01:30:59.078
- You're working with them.
- No.

661
01:30:59.206 --> 01:31:02.621
- I want the truth.
- I am telling the truth.

662
01:31:02.750 --> 01:31:06.499
Sanchez has arranged to buy four
Stinger missiles from the Contras.

663
01:31:06.629 --> 01:31:09.915
He'll shoot down an American airliner
if the DEA doesn't lay off.

664
01:31:10.050 --> 01:31:13.964
- What about you and Heller?
- Felix gave me a letter at his wedding.

665
01:31:14.095 --> 01:31:18.424
granting Heller immunity
if he gets the Stingers back.

666
01:31:19.809 --> 01:31:22.597
Did he go for the deal?

667
01:31:22.729 --> 01:31:24.768
Yes.

668
01:31:25.148 --> 01:31:31.020
And then you missed Sanchez. and Heller
panicked and he said the deal was off.

669
01:31:31.154 --> 01:31:33.776
and that I was dead
if he ever saw me again.

670
01:31:35.742 --> 01:31:39.361
There's more to this
than your personal vendetta.

671
01:31:44.459 --> 01:31:46.499
It's a mess.

672
01:31:47.962 --> 01:31:51.379
Sanchez has tripled his security.

673
01:31:53.094 --> 01:31:56.094
You'll never get another shot at him.

674
01:32:01.476 --> 01:32:03.516
We don't have to.

675
01:32:05.856 --> 01:32:10.565
Meet me at the harbour master's office in
two hours. Q. bring the Rolls to the front.

676
01:32:10.695 --> 01:32:12.354
Yes. sir.

677
01:32:14.281 --> 01:32:15.776
Señor Bond.

678
01:32:15.908 --> 01:32:19.158
Señor Montelongo.
I'm making a withdrawal.

679
01:32:37.888 --> 01:32:40.558
Pilot coming aboard. sir.

680
01:32:43.769 --> 01:32:46.557
Well? Take me to the bridge.

681
01:32:52.404 --> 01:32:57.112
- Gracias. Captain. I'll take over now.
- You? You're the harbour pilot?

682
01:32:57.242 --> 01:32:59.530
No. I'm his secretary!

683
01:32:59.660 --> 01:33:02.116
All yours. sir... Ma'am.

684
01:33:17.845 --> 01:33:19.885
Aren't you going in a bit too fast?

685
01:33:20.015 --> 01:33:23.466
You wanna do the driving?
You take the wheel.

686
01:33:32.736 --> 01:33:34.812
Full speed astern.

687
01:33:40.828 --> 01:33:45.454
- What the hell are you doing?
- Harbour pilot went crazy.

688
01:34:20.785 --> 01:34:24.913
- I'd stick to flying if I were you.
- I got the job done.

689
01:34:36.592 --> 01:34:40.591
Franz. What a surprise.
I didn't think you'd be here.

690
01:34:40.722 --> 01:34:43.177
Yeah. I like surprises.

691
01:34:47.478 --> 01:34:50.764
You seem to be having
a lot of problems lately.

692
01:34:50.899 --> 01:34:54.647
Well. we had this crazy harbour pilot.

693
01:34:55.111 --> 01:34:57.899
Let's talk about the money you owe me.

694
01:34:59.615 --> 01:35:01.026
Let's talk inside.

695
01:35:07.248 --> 01:35:10.866
- Does he have a safe?
- Not up here. Maybe below.

696
01:35:12.128 --> 01:35:13.788
Have a look around.

697
01:35:15.590 --> 01:35:18.544
Check the bow
and give me a damage report.

698
01:35:26.226 --> 01:35:30.722
Do I have this right? He water-skied
behind the plane. jumps on it...

699
01:35:30.855 --> 01:35:34.225
No. He was...

700
01:35:34.360 --> 01:35:38.143
Well. yeah.
He threw the pilots out and flew away.

701
01:35:39.323 --> 01:35:42.359
Like a little bird.

702
01:35:50.960 --> 01:35:52.998
The knife.

703
01:36:10.313 --> 01:36:11.771
Pedro.

704
01:36:26.788 --> 01:36:29.408
Would I make up a story like that?

705
01:36:29.540 --> 01:36:32.031
You must have seen something.

706
01:36:43.179 --> 01:36:45.635
- Where's 007?
- He's coming.

707
01:36:59.612 --> 01:37:01.985
That's not my money. I swear.

708
01:37:02.115 --> 01:37:05.530
That's right. amigo. It's mine.

709
01:37:09.206 --> 01:37:12.159
You think I'm stupid?

710
01:37:12.417 --> 01:37:16.331
You rip me off. then use my own money
to pay someone to kill me?

711
01:37:16.713 --> 01:37:19.797
You want it so bad? Then take it!

712
01:37:22.969 --> 01:37:26.588
What are you doin'? Wait. Let me talk.

713
01:37:26.723 --> 01:37:29.392
This is not my money!

714
01:37:31.061 --> 01:37:33.101
No!

715
01:37:33.647 --> 01:37:35.520
What the...

716
01:37:36.525 --> 01:37:38.565
That hurts. Please!

717
01:37:42.823 --> 01:37:45.112
What are you doing?

718
01:37:46.868 --> 01:37:48.446
Sanchez.

719
01:37:56.587 --> 01:37:59.457
Please. Franz. No!

720
01:38:14.021 --> 01:38:16.476
What about the money. patron?

721
01:38:18.943 --> 01:38:20.354
Launder it.

722
01:38:37.503 --> 01:38:40.872
This is where you leave. Take the plane.
I'll see you both in Miami.

723
01:38:41.006 --> 01:38:43.676
- Aren't you coming?
- No. They'll be after me.

724
01:38:43.801 --> 01:38:46.256
It'll be safer on my own.

725
01:38:58.608 --> 01:39:00.647
Come on. my dear.

726
01:39:09.994 --> 01:39:12.034
See you later.

727
01:39:16.167 --> 01:39:19.667
- What's that?
- Bond's clothes. They're clean.

728
01:39:36.897 --> 01:39:39.305
Sorry to wake you. hermano.

729
01:39:44.530 --> 01:39:48.029
I thought you'd like to know
the information you gave me paid off.

730
01:39:48.367 --> 01:39:52.067
- I got the guy who set me up.
- Only one guy?

731
01:39:53.288 --> 01:39:56.622
- What do you mean?
- I just thought that...

732
01:39:58.001 --> 01:40:02.249
no one'd be stupid enough
to try to take you on on their own.

733
01:40:13.142 --> 01:40:16.974
- I want you to come with me tomorrow.
- Where are we going?

734
01:40:17.771 --> 01:40:20.144
It's a surprise. You're gonna like it.

735
01:40:35.206 --> 01:40:39.867
- James. what are you doing back here?
- Your being here's not a good idea. Lupe.

736
01:40:40.002 --> 01:40:43.621
It's all right. Franz is having
dinner with the Chinese.

737
01:40:45.175 --> 01:40:48.674
- Where's he taking me tomorrow?
- He's showing them a special place.

738
01:40:48.803 --> 01:40:54.426
I don't know where. James. don't go.
I'm scared. What's gonna happen to us?

739
01:40:54.559 --> 01:40:58.058
Don't worry. When this is all over.
I'll make sure you get back home.

740
01:40:58.187 --> 01:41:02.980
Home? It took me 1 5 years to get away
from there. I don't wanna go back.

741
01:41:04.736 --> 01:41:08.319
Can't we leave together?
I'll be safe with you.

742
01:41:13.829 --> 01:41:16.449
No. Lupe. I don't think
that would work out.

743
01:41:17.207 --> 01:41:19.449
How can we tell unless we try?

744
01:41:26.675 --> 01:41:29.462
I think it's gonna work out very well.

745
01:41:36.727 --> 01:41:39.182
All right. I'll answer it.

746
01:41:42.107 --> 01:41:47.861
Miss Kennedy. I saw you at the casino
with James. We need to speak in private.

747
01:41:48.238 --> 01:41:52.152
- It's all right. He's with me.
- James is in danger. Sanchez is no fool.

748
01:41:52.284 --> 01:41:56.910
He is checking up on him. You know.
if they find anything suspicious...

749
01:41:57.038 --> 01:41:59.612
It's all right.
He's out of the country by now.

750
01:41:59.750 --> 01:42:03.450
You don't understand.
Last night he stayed with me.

751
01:42:06.715 --> 01:42:10.084
- At Sanchez' house?
- Si. Franz is taking him on a trip.

752
01:42:10.219 --> 01:42:12.176
They leave in an hour.

753
01:42:12.304 --> 01:42:16.800
If anything happens to him. I don't know
what I'll do. I love James so much.

754
01:42:16.934 --> 01:42:22.355
You must go before you're missed. Now.
don't worry. We'll think of something.

755
01:42:23.482 --> 01:42:28.144
"I love James so much."
I'll be damned if I'll help him.

756
01:42:28.279 --> 01:42:32.857
Look. don't judge him too harshly.
my dear. Field operatives often use

757
01:42:32.992 --> 01:42:37.286
every means at their disposal
to achieve their objectives.

758
01:42:37.413 --> 01:42:39.452
Bullshit.

759
01:42:52.887 --> 01:42:55.509
Bond's just left in convoy.
Two cars and a Jeep.

760
01:42:55.640 --> 01:42:59.720
- Turning north onto the main highway.
- I copy that. Q.

761
01:43:09.112 --> 01:43:11.650
What are you doing to my plane?

762
01:43:11.781 --> 01:43:14.984
Overhaul. Señor Sanchez order it.

763
01:43:17.454 --> 01:43:20.289
I must have a plane.
Where can I rent one?

764
01:43:21.833 --> 01:43:23.873
No planes.

765
01:43:34.179 --> 01:43:38.047
You brought the Stingers.
From now on I want them close to me.

766
01:44:09.923 --> 01:44:16.176
We started this place strictly as a cover.
but Professor Joe turns a tidy profit.

767
01:44:39.578 --> 01:44:42.829
Welcome. This way. please.

768
01:44:42.957 --> 01:44:46.326
I'm going to have to ask that
each of you put on one of these.

769
01:44:46.461 --> 01:44:51.039
It's for your own safety.
so I'm sure you'll understand.

770
01:44:51.173 --> 01:44:55.717
We can't have our best customers
developing a drug habit.

771
01:44:57.305 --> 01:44:59.345
This way. gentlemen.

772
01:45:36.762 --> 01:45:41.471
Our product dissolves completely
in ordinary gasoline.

773
01:45:41.600 --> 01:45:44.600
making it absolutely undetectable.

774
01:45:49.316 --> 01:45:53.528
- How do you get it back?
- You want us to tell you all our secrets?

775
01:45:54.155 --> 01:45:58.104
Before we're partners?
Take them to the lab.

776
01:45:58.242 --> 01:46:00.282
This way. gentlemen.

777
01:46:11.046 --> 01:46:14.996
- Who's the new guy?
- Somebody I thought could be useful.

778
01:46:27.605 --> 01:46:30.642
- Can I help you?
- I have a surprise for Professor Joe.

779
01:46:30.775 --> 01:46:34.986
- Sorry. No visitors this week.
- I came all the way from Wichita Falls.

780
01:46:35.113 --> 01:46:37.485
- I'm sorry.
- We took up a collection.

781
01:46:37.616 --> 01:46:40.188
We wanted Professor Joe
to accept it personally.

782
01:46:42.579 --> 01:46:45.663
You may remove
your masks now. gentlemen.

783
01:46:46.541 --> 01:46:48.997
So. do we have a deal?

784
01:46:52.338 --> 01:46:55.090
The terms were 100 million

785
01:46:55.217 --> 01:46:59.000
in negotiable bearer bonds
from each of you.

786
01:47:10.357 --> 01:47:12.813
Professor Joe. It's really you!

787
01:47:15.153 --> 01:47:17.027
It's magnificent.

788
01:47:17.155 --> 01:47:21.817
Rebuilt stone for stone and restored
to all of its original glory.

789
01:47:21.952 --> 01:47:26.245
- Is this for me?
- Yes. I almost forgot. I got so flustered...

790
01:47:27.374 --> 01:47:31.158
Tell me. child. have you ever
thought of studying here?

791
01:47:31.295 --> 01:47:36.087
- Would that be possible?
- Come. Let's see if you have the aptitude.

792
01:47:36.216 --> 01:47:38.255
To a long association.

793
01:47:39.094 --> 01:47:42.048
- What's the process?
- It's very simple.

794
01:47:44.266 --> 01:47:48.311
An 18 per cent mixture of cocaine
and ordinary gasoline.

795
01:47:49.688 --> 01:47:51.811
Just keep quiet.

796
01:48:14.838 --> 01:48:18.967
We already have your first shipment
being loaded into the four tanker trucks.

797
01:48:19.343 --> 01:48:21.383
Welcome. my dear.

798
01:48:22.889 --> 01:48:24.763
Please join me.

799
01:48:26.100 --> 01:48:28.140
Wow.

800
01:48:30.188 --> 01:48:33.936
This is my humble sanctuary.
away from the cares of the world.

801
01:48:34.066 --> 01:48:37.316
Your own private meditation chamber.

802
01:48:37.444 --> 01:48:41.146
Built from the sacred rocks
of the original temple.

803
01:48:44.327 --> 01:48:49.701
I did have it soundproofed.
so nothing will disturb our meditation.

804
01:48:54.087 --> 01:48:58.167
- I brought you another surprise.
- I love surprises. Where is it?

805
01:49:09.227 --> 01:49:11.386
Look. this really isn't necessary.

806
01:49:13.982 --> 01:49:16.438
Give me the keys.

807
01:49:29.540 --> 01:49:31.199
Bless your heart.

808
01:49:31.416 --> 01:49:34.501
Your monthly delivery
will be by ocean-going tanker.

809
01:49:34.628 --> 01:49:39.504
We'll send our chief chemist along
to supervise the reconversion process.

810
01:49:40.050 --> 01:49:43.134
You keep the gas as a bonus.

811
01:49:44.554 --> 01:49:48.469
And if there's a problem
with customs. no evidence.

812
01:50:10.539 --> 01:50:12.828
I know him. He's an informer.

813
01:50:15.461 --> 01:50:17.537
You disappoint me.

814
01:50:17.672 --> 01:50:21.621
Who are you working for? Tell me.

815
01:50:26.180 --> 01:50:28.636
You don't wanna talk?

816
01:50:42.405 --> 01:50:46.403
I can get the trucks out.
but I don't think I can control the fire.

817
01:50:46.534 --> 01:50:50.282
Forget the fire. Get some cars.
We're gonna take the tankers with us.

818
01:50:50.413 --> 01:50:53.249
Wait a minute.
This setup cost us 32 million.

819
01:50:53.375 --> 01:50:56.541
- We have to try and save it.
- I don't give a shit about the setup.

820
01:50:56.669 --> 01:51:01.212
We've got 500 million in the case and
20 tons of Colombian pure in the tankers.

821
01:51:01.340 --> 01:51:04.046
- Go help Heller.
- We have a deal with the Orientals.

822
01:51:04.177 --> 01:51:06.928
- We've got their money.
- I said go help Heller.

823
01:51:14.646 --> 01:51:17.813
Now. do you wanna
make this hard or easy?

824
01:51:22.696 --> 01:51:25.151
Put him in the conveyor.

825
01:51:36.376 --> 01:51:39.662
When you're up to your ankles.
you'll beg to tell me everything.

826
01:51:39.797 --> 01:51:43.545
When you're up to your knees.
you'll kiss my ass to kill you.

827
01:51:48.388 --> 01:51:52.636
I'm the least of your problems. If you
couldn't trust Krest. who can you trust?

828
01:51:57.189 --> 01:52:00.558
Who's got your 500 million?
Truman-Lodge?

829
01:52:04.238 --> 01:52:06.693
What about the Stingers?

830
01:52:09.994 --> 01:52:12.531
What do you know about Stingers?

831
01:52:14.957 --> 01:52:17.875
We gotta go. patron.
This place'll blow up any second.

832
01:52:18.002 --> 01:52:20.041
- Where's Heller?
- I don't know.

833
01:52:20.171 --> 01:52:24.417
That's the last you'll see
of Heller and your Stingers.

834
01:52:28.179 --> 01:52:30.337
Thanks for the advice.

835
01:52:43.361 --> 01:52:47.229
Have my car meet me up at the top.
Come with me.

836
01:53:24.778 --> 01:53:28.562
- You're dead.
- You took the words out of my mouth.

837
01:53:39.752 --> 01:53:41.495
Sanchez!

838
01:53:48.635 --> 01:53:52.799
- Are you all right?
- Switch the bloody machine off.

839
01:54:06.361 --> 01:54:09.197
Hey. I was making sure
these were secure.

840
01:54:10.283 --> 01:54:12.405
It's a good idea.

841
01:54:12.534 --> 01:54:15.156
- Take them up to my car.
- Of course.

842
01:54:59.624 --> 01:55:03.456
- Oh. God. It's Heller.
- Yeah. Looks like he came to a dead end.

843
01:55:03.587 --> 01:55:05.626
Come on.

844
01:55:29.612 --> 01:55:31.652
You. Come with me.

845
01:55:50.300 --> 01:55:52.340
Come on.

846
01:56:06.942 --> 01:56:09.350
Surprise!

847
01:56:10.488 --> 01:56:11.898
Bless your heart.

848
01:57:59.890 --> 01:58:01.847
Perez.

849
01:58:01.976 --> 01:58:05.060
Bond has escaped.
Meet me at Paso del Diablo.

850
01:58:55.655 --> 01:58:58.407
Don't worry. It's only money.

851
02:01:20.344 --> 02:01:22.383
Oh. no.

852
02:01:24.765 --> 02:01:25.678
Shit!

853
02:01:38.153 --> 02:01:40.192
Brilliant.

854
02:01:41.073 --> 02:01:46.233
Well done. Franz.
Another 80 million dollar write-off.

855
02:01:46.995 --> 02:01:50.531
I guess it's time
to start cutting overhead.

856
02:04:57.605 --> 02:05:00.097
James.

857
02:06:55.350 --> 02:06:59.727
- You could have had everything.
- Don't you want to know why?

858
02:07:56.244 --> 02:07:58.487
Well. what are you waiting for? Get in.

859
02:07:59.999 --> 02:08:01.624
Yes. sir.

860
02:08:14.096 --> 02:08:18.557
- I'll be up to see you next week.
- Good. I'll be out by then. M called.

861
02:08:18.685 --> 02:08:22.184
He tried to reach you.
I think he may have a job for you.

862
02:08:22.313 --> 02:08:25.433
Look. Felix. I have to go.
My hostess has just arrived.

863
02:08:25.567 --> 02:08:28.022
- Take care. James.
- You too. Goodbye.

864
02:08:31.197 --> 02:08:36.239
- I thought you hated that thing.
- Iguanas are a girl's best friend.

865
02:08:43.585 --> 02:08:46.372
- Well. here's to you. my dear.
- Cheers.

866
02:08:48.715 --> 02:08:51.253
Thank you for everything. James.

867
02:08:54.346 --> 02:08:56.385
Thank you.

868
02:09:08.318 --> 02:09:10.774
You could stay here with me.

869
02:09:12.156 --> 02:09:14.194
Excuse me.

870
02:09:25.252 --> 02:09:29.166
I think you and el presidente
will make a perfect couple.

871
02:10:01.205 --> 02:10:04.372
Why don't you wait until you're asked?

872
02:10:04.500 --> 02:10:06.956
So why don't you ask me?

873
02:10:07.305 --> 02:11:07.913
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm
